sentences: Paul Craft (August 12, 1938 – October 18, 2014) was an American singer-songwriter.
Between 1977 and 1978, Craft charted three singles on RCA Nashville.

His song "Keep Me From Blowing Away" was originally recorded by The Seldom Scene on their 1973 album Act II and was then recorded by Linda Ronstadt on her 1974 album Heart Like a Wheel, and has since been recorded by Moe Bandy, T. Graham Brown, Jerry Lee Lewis, The Grascals and Willie Nelson.

His song "Keep Me From Blowing Away" was originally recorded by The Seldom Scene on their 1973 album Act II and was then recorded by Linda Ronstadt on her 1974 album Heart Like a Wheel, and has since been recorded by Moe Bandy, T. Graham Brown, Jerry Lee Lewis, The Grascals and Willie Nelson.
His song "Midnight Flyer" was recorded by the Eagles.
His song "Dropkick Me, Jesus" was a No. 17 country hit for Bobby Bare in 1976.
Craft was inducted into the Nashville Songwriters Hall of Fame on October 5, 2014.
Craft died at a hospital in Nashville, Tennessee on October 18, 2014, at the age of 76.
Paul Craft Interview NAMM Oral History Library (2009)
